[Student "S"]
{South is to play 7NT. West leads the \SQ.

One more winner is needed. Dummy's fourth \C is a possibility.

So take the \SK and play \C A K Q.

West discards a \S on the third \C. 

Now you know East guards the \Cs.

Before tackling \Ds, see what you can discover about \Ss.

Play the \SA. East discards a \H. 

East guards the \Cs. West guards the \Ss. Nobody can guard the \Hs.

Play 4 rounds of \Ds. 

[showcards N:S9,H6,D4,C8 E:HQ,H9,H8,CJ S:S7,HA,HK,H5 W:SJ,HJ,HT,H7]

On the fourth \D East had to discard a \H. You discarded a small \S. West discarded a \S on the third \D and a \H on the fourth.

Play dummy's \D4. East cannot throw the \CJ or he will set up dummy's \C8, so he discards a \H.

You discard the \S7.

Now West is squeezed. He cannot discard the \SJ or he will set up dummy's \S9, so he discards a \H.

You win the last three \H tricks with another Double Squeeze.}
[Play "W"]SQ

